:parcel <<'/---'
Handle *character setters* (i.e., functions setting the values of character
variables).
/---

# ....................{ SETTERS                            }....................
:func.document <<'/---'
void :set_char_to_char(string int_name, int number)

Set the value of the passed character variable to the passed character: e.g.,

.:set_char_to_char()
==========================================
[source]
------------------------------------------
>>> :int zed
>>> :set_char_to_char zed Z
>>> :string.output "${zed}"
Z
------------------------------------------
==========================================
/---
function :set_char_to_char() {
    # Validate sanity.
    die_unless_args_2 'Expected one character name and one character.'
    :string char_name__sctc="${1}" char__sctc="${2}"
    :var.die_unless_type_char "${char_name__sctc}"
    :die_unless_char "${char__sctc}"

    # Set such character.
    noop ${(P)char_name__sctc::=${char__sctc}}
}

# --------------------( WASTELANDS                         )--------------------
